===Verb===
{{en-verb|shrinks|shrinking|shrank|past2=shrunk|shrunk|past_ptc2=shrunken}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause to become [[smaller]].
#: {{ux|en|The dryer '''shrank''' my sweater.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2008|month=October|author=David Schipper|title=Outsmart your stomach: Seven ways to fill your gut—and lose it, too|journal={{w|Men's Health}}|volume=23|issue=8|issn=1054-4836|page={{gbooks|VMgDAAAAMBAJ|135|shrink}}|passage=The bottom line is this: To '''shrink''' your gut, you need to start listening to it.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To become smaller; to [[contract]].
#: {{ux|en|This garment will '''shrink''' when [[wet]].}}
#* {{RQ:Bacon Sylva Sylvarum|passage=I have not found that water, by mixture of ashes, will '''shrink''' or draw into less room.}}
#* {{RQ:Dryden AM}}
#*: And '''shrink''' like parchment in consuming fire.
#* '''2018''', [https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/china-s-melting-glacier-brings-visitors-concern-over-climate-change/4627742.html VOA Learning English > China's Melting Glacier Brings Visitors, Adds to Climate Concerns]
#*: Since 1982, it has '''shrunk''' by 250 meters. [[File:Since 1982, it has shrunk by 250 meters.ogg]]
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2021 October 6|author=Greg Morse|title=A need for speed and the drive for 125|journal=RAIL|issue=941|page=52|text=When they took over the 1000 'Flying Scotsman' from May 1979, the journey from London to Edinburgh '''shrank''' to just 4hrs 37mins - including a stop at Newcastle.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[cower]] or [[flinch]].
#: {{ux|en|Molly '''shrank''' away from the blows of the whip.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To draw back; to withdraw.
#* {{RQ:Milton Poems|poem=Nativity|page=10|passage=The Libyc ''Hammon'' '''ſhrinks''' his horn,}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|figuratively}} To withdraw or retire, as from danger.
#* {{RQ:Pope Man|chapter=III|passage=What happier natures '''shrink''' at with affright, / The hard inhabitant contends is right.}}
#* '''1881''', {{w|Benjamin Jowett}} (translator), ''Thucydides''
#*: They assisted us against the Thebans when you '''shrank''' from the task.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To move back or away, especially because of fear or disgust.

